reviews.name: Saint Francis Hospital Vinita

reviews_data.review_text: After my daughter's accident that required stitches on the way home from our family vacation and not knowing where we were. We found y'all. Your staff was so nice and understanding. Had no problems at all with getting her seen and taken care of. Thank you so much for the kindness you showed my family during this time.

Well if they had a negative  stars iwould put negative  5 went up there tonight because  my blood suger was at 500 in a diabetic  and the whole experience  was horrible almost gave my way to much insulin then laughed about it and when my blood results  came back i have kidney  failure so they put me in the nastiest  room the had the ER  doctor  acted like all i wanted was pills and told me he wasent going to help me with a hi. The the iv line came undone shooting water everywhere  and the lady nurse thought that was just so funny needless to say i told them to give me discharge  papers that i would reather go home and deal with it there they dident even argue they said ok no big deal how is this hospital  even still open how they are the rudest judgemental  place i have ever seen. So heres my rating.     NEGATIVE  10 STARS.  I will have this hospital  investigated for not doing their job this was a horrible  experience  screw that place
ER.Staff was very professional, seen in a timely manner. Will go back when needed.
Lovely!  He even made me a birthday banner and wrote me a sweet note!

I went in on a Sat. evening with a Recluse Spider Bite I had for 30 hrs. They were quick to get me back. The staff was kind compassionate and friendly. The Dr. Came in right away away and got an  IV flowing with antibiotics and fluids. I was very comforted and impressed with the new change. My discharge instructions were very explicit and easy to read. I am just grateful they were there.

I had an issue with incorrect coding on a visit, so began a appeal with my insurance. I explained this to St Francis, whose rep put in my account chart. Immediately after this I got a letter from their collection agency who I proved appeal process to and they sent info to St Francis. After that I immediately began being harassed weekly about my account. I even made small payments to stop harassment, since I knew my appeal would take awhile but be successful. Even with the small payments, the harassment still persisted every week! This organization is the worst!!!!

Hospital does not know how to give information to there bill company so your bill get mess up for workers compensation claims.  You need to provide all information to your bill department and make sure information is correct.

They are really judging  especially the little tiny Dr with the beard he thinks he knows about the medical field but knows nothing they couldn't even tell me what was wrong with me and Dr Hitesman just like little man there young and no nothing 😆😅🤣😂
Uncaring to COVID19 patients and their families.  I miss Craig General.  St. Francis is the worst hospital ever!!!!!  Myself or anyone else in my family will NOT be back... I can promise you that.
If I could rate 0 stars I would!!! Took my mother in law just for lab work and we are still waiting here and have been here almost 2 hours. I miss Craig General!!!
One of the best care giver hospitals and ER experiences I have ever had! Superb staff all the way around!

I went there and found a doctor that really took time to get to know me ,she is awesome but now I come to find out she will no longer be there,she might of took time but unlike warran clinic where they take 5 min and are not compassionate this lady was very caring,they had me in the ER in Miami where I was there four hours just to tell me he didn't know what was wrong and there wanting her to hurry ,not right at all .😥😥😥
They took really great care of my daughter a few months ago and they took good care of my wife the doctor was very informative and the nurses were very nice thnks to all of them
